newspaper_data.title: Church Ministers to Gay Community
newspaper_data.entry: On January 22, 1984, the Los Angeles Times reported on the West Hollywood Presbyterian Church, located at 7350 Sunset Boulevard, and its ministering to and inclusion of the gay community. The LA Times also details the church’s past of ministering to “senior citizens, ex-convicts, hippies, hookers, unwed mothers and drug addicts.” During the 1960’s, when, according to the LA Times, there were “long-haired radicals who were drawn to Hollywood and sleeping in its streets,” the church sheltered around 1,000 people a month at the height of the decade. The church later went on to found the Lazarus Project, the first outreach ministry to gay men within the Presbyterian Church.
